    {
      "start": 437.58,
      "end": 438.06,
      "text": "멋지다."
    },
    {
      "start": 438.08,
      "end": 439.38,
      "text": "All the singers like the singer."
    },
    {
      "start": 439.38,
      "end": 439.82,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 440.08,
      "end": 445.06,
      "text": "This guy was respected by many actors for his stage, television, and film work."
    },
    {
      "start": 445.16,
      "end": 445.5,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 445.52,
      "end": 450.3,
      "text": "He was in over 180 films and in many TV and stage productions."
    },
    {
      "start": 450.54,
      "end": 450.86,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 451.22,
      "end": 457.52,
      "text": "And he actually, he was in college and he left to spend some years in the U.S. Marines,"
    },
    {
      "start": 457.92,
      "end": 458.52,
      "text": "Haibyongdae."
    },
    {
      "start": 458.6,
      "end": 460.26,
      "text": "And he was stationed in Korea."
    },
    {
      "start": 460.52,
      "end": 461.02,
      "text": "Oh, really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 461.02,
      "end": 464.24,
      "text": "So he came to Korea way back in the late 1950s."
    },
    {
      "start": 464.3,
      "end": 464.58,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 464.84,
      "end": 465.82,
      "text": "After the Korean War."
    },
    {
      "start": 465.82,
      "end": 472.12,
      "text": "And then he went back and he went to Columbia, where he majored in history, which is my major."
    },
    {
      "start": 472.3,
      "end": 473.22,
      "text": "Ah, 역사."
    },
    {
      "start": 473.34,
      "end": 474.34,
      "text": "I can appreciate this."
    },
    {
      "start": 474.4,
      "end": 474.68,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 475.22,
      "end": 477.38,
      "text": "And then he started working in regional theater."
    },
    {
      "start": 477.58,
      "end": 484.16,
      "text": "And he supported his theater work with blue-collar jobs, like driving a taxi and bartending."
    },
    {
      "start": 484.6,
      "end": 486.92,
      "text": "And he just worked his way up from the bottom."
    },
    {
      "start": 486.92,
      "end": 489.7,
      "text": "So I have a lot of respect for his career path."
    },
    {
      "start": 490.84,
      "end": 498.38,
      "text": "Career 뿐 아니라 정말 인생 자체가 많은 사람들로부터 존경을 받을 법한 사람이구나 라는 생각을 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 498.6,
      "end": 501.18,
      "text": "He won a Golden Globe Award for Best Actor."
    },
    {
      "start": 501.3,
      "end": 501.64,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 502.04,
      "end": 507.86,
      "text": "For his role in the television film Death of a Salesman, which is also a world-famous play."
    },
    {
      "start": 508.02,
      "end": 508.42,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 508.64,
      "end": 512.4,
      "text": "A Salesman의 죽음이라는 영화에서 열연을 했다고 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 512.4,
      "end": 516.8,
      "text": "That is much more familiar for Americans than the Seagull."
    },
    {
      "start": 516.92,
      "end": 522.6,
      "text": "But he is very talented and versatile in many different plays, movies, and TV shows."
